{"name":"Domion Table","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.deadlands-rules.Tables-Deadlands.EsFQ9n1RsygZb1Js"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"Roll on this table whenever a Harrowed lets the devil out (or draw a Dominion Card if you have them).","results":[{"_id":"KxwEWoNlacPYCKiN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Magic:</strong> The demon draws Hellish power straight from the deepest part of the Hunting Grounds. It gives friends and foes within 5\" (10 yards) +2 to Trait and damage rolls for the next five rounds. Those with an Arcane Background that uses Power Points recover 10 points. Best of all, the raw display galvanizes the host's will. She gains 1 point of Dominion.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9d4r4qTYb2c4oFOv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Malevolence:</strong> The Harrowed's allies witness the true demonic nature of the manitou. Everyone who can see the thing clearly (GM's call) or is within 5\" (10 yards) must make an immediate Fear check at –2.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MsPVgj7sKQGl6Wg1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Mischief:</strong> The Harrowed must make a Spirit roll at –2 or lose 1 point of Dominion. At some point, the demon takes control and causes trouble for the hero or his companions. The manitou might loosen a friend's saddle when he isn't looking, throw an ally's ammo into a river, or find a way to use his companions' Hindrances and backgrounds to start fights or otherwise cause strife.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"XnR0AmhS4lvWCXga","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Misfortune:</strong> The demon taunts the Harrowed with her failures, dark secrets, or tragic past, chipping away at her will. The hero must make a Spirit roll or lose 1 Dominion point.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5NfWoZhZ5bN6WIQf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Mayhem:</strong> As Mischief, but the deed is bigger or more vicious and the Spirit roll is made at –4.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IhtKV6SXItJY9a5s","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Murder:</strong> The host loses 1 point of Dominion. The demon goes full psycho and murders someone. It might fire a \"stray\" shot at some troublesome hero right away, or it might wait to slip away and kill a stranger, innocent, or even one of the host's loved ones.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"Xk9rGSTg8lxfgxZ0"}
{"name":"Huckster Backfire Table","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.deadlands-rules.Tables-Deadlands.YNmB0Z5Zqq9jF10D"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"When a huckster Deals with the Devil and rolls a Critical Failure (see page 66), roll on the Backfire Table to see what the manitou does to the unfortunate gambler.","results":[{"_id":"iNXHEXeLSdWXvt61","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Mindwipe:</strong> The manitou fries the huckster's mind with energy channeled from the darkest parts of the Hunting Grounds. Her Spellcasting die permanently drops one type.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"TySOEE5WtsQrA2T1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Brain Drain:</strong> As Mindwipe, but the effect lasts only until the end of the encounter.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[2,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7x8GNN44jWniHCIY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Corruption:</strong> The spell is twisted to have the worst possible result for the huckster. Damage-causing spells affect her or her allies, <em>protection</em> aids her foes, information-gathering incantations lie, and so on.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[4,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9bgAUHDdrmzvXi4I","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Overload:</strong> Supernatural energy overwhelms the huckster. She's Distracted, Stunned, and Vulnerable!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[9,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"nEvty3XtqhbvVm7F","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Backlash:</strong> The manitou overloads the huckster's nervous system with eldritch energy. She suffers 2d6 damage plus the number of Power Points she needed to successfully activate the power.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[13,16],"drawn":false},{"_id":"kolPZ8DtuoE5cUpg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Madness:</strong> The manitou drives the huckster insane. Roll on the mad scientist's <strong>Madness Table</strong> (page 89). The condition lasts one week.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[17,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"4wCDCV0VIlDctTjU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Dirty Dealer:</strong> The huckster catches the manitou cheating. Immediately after the hand is resolved, she's Shaken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"vQpH1LBEQA3gjFHs"}
{"name":"Mad Science Malfunction Table","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.deadlands-rules.Tables-Deadlands.zyVWyYciOCXwgrVF"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"Roll on the Malfunction Table when a mad scientist gets a Critical Failure on a Weird Science roll.","results":[{"_id":"NWbcKAzXMERpI2ik","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Mindwipe:</strong> The manitou fries part of the mad scientist’s mind. The inventor’s Weird Science die drops one level permanently.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"87SrhDjmTyCrD9kV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Madness:</strong> Roll on the <strong>Madness Table</strong> below. The condition is permanent.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[2,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pCObOe7IML9CldrV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Kaboom!:</strong> The device explodes for [[3d6]] in a Large Blast Template!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[4,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8DlIdAn2YcazEYG3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Breakdown:</strong> The item requires extensive repairs and can’t be used again this encounter.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[7,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Aq3tWGDueVoDUmap","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Gremlin:</strong> The device attracts [[2d6]] gremlins from the Hunting Grounds! See page 168.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[11,14],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZqXScVXBdRoWGgwT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Mishap:</strong> The inventor takes Fatigue and all currently maintained powers stop working.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[15,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ADGgNRcCujkfZXHO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Glitch:</strong> The item can’t be used until a Repair roll is made as an action.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VrYKN1fQwc9tP5qG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Temporary Madness:</strong> Roll on the <strong>Madness Table</strong> below. The condition is permanent. The condition lasts one week.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"Zd3BUHYgEVPRO2bL","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"m5FCP4FMfhXG10Vi"}
{"name":"Madness Table","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.deadlands-rules.Tables-Deadlands.Zd3BUHYgEVPRO2bL"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"If a result gives the scientist a Hindrance he already has, increase a Minor version to the Major version. If he already has the Major version, roll again.","results":[{"_id":"rc2abRrNPzsiEKEN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Absent-Minded:</strong> The character forgets little details. He might forget to boil his coffee, wear pants, or cinch his saddle. He gains the Clueless Hindrance.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[1,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VstECKfVj62oizUI","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Delusion:</strong> The inventor comes to believe something patently untrue. Maybe he thinks a member of the party is a werewolf or the sky is blue because the \"Moon People\" paint it that way every morning. He gains the Delusional (Minor) Hindrance.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[3,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"iA5d772rGV3tRwQF","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Eccentricity:</strong> The scientist becomes more eccentric. Maybe he smothers his food in vinegar or eats lots of bran to keep his digestive system clear. The condition is basically harmless and amusing though occasionally annoying. He now has the Minor Quirk Hindrance.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[5,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pbTFeyeKDzoayQvA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Evil Deeds:</strong> An insidious manitou convinces the hero someone or something is evil and must be stopped. Each time he gets this result increases his mania. At first he may only talk badly about his \"enemies.\" Later on he might attempt to ruin or even kill them.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[7,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"3alscf9zrGCz8yhu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Phobia:</strong> The scientist develops a strange fear of something completely irrational. He gains a Phobia (Minor) Hindrance the first time this comes up. It increases to a Major Phobia if it comes up again. If it comes up a third time he gains a new Minor Phobia.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[9,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"K15FplmLFXR9Me5E","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Mumbler:</strong> The engineer talks to himself constantly and his sentences often trail off into meaningless drivel. He occasionally hears voices talking back, as well, and feels compelled to listen. This gives him the Impulsive Hindrance. And sometimes those voices might be real!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[11,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"xcWOJvcYYrMc2HPr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Paranoia:</strong> Everyone's out to steal the inventor's ideas, or so he believes. Or maybe sinister creatures from \"Dimension X\" are following his work so they can steal it and conquer the Earth! The inventor gains the Jealous Hindrance (Minor) in addition to his general paranoia.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[13,14],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7aVqqQxttKrNztYk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Madness:</strong> Choose a new Minor Hindrance that reflects mental instability each time this result comes up. Work with the player to explain how his character is affected by this new madness.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[15,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"g1wBCXuTwOgNcYfa","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Moment of Clarity:</strong> Things suddenly make sense for the inventor in some strange way. She gains Conviction, and may instantly remove any one madness condition obtained previously, if she has any.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"Jbr7DxbFPLd8IIBQ"}
{"name":"Malfunctions","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.deadlands-rules.Tables-Deadlands.b4GXcmCCLivyO7EI"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"When rolling a Trait to use an infernal device, a Critical Failure indicates a Malfunction. Roll on the table below to determine just how bad things are about to get. For armor, Malfunctions occur when a Critical Failure is made on a Soak roll, which is really the worst possible time for things to go south, isn’t it?","results":[{"_id":"DRdza0EO8F7uc8AB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Catastrophic:</strong> Vehicles and powered items explode for [[3d6]] damage in a Large Blast Template. Non-powered devices Stun the user and cause [[2d6]] damage as the ghost rock ignites, goggles shatter, spring boots propel the user into a wall, etc. Armor doesn’t protect against consumables that are injected, inhaled, or swallowed!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[1,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Kw8GBb1pkvh0pK2G","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Major:</strong> The item breaks down and requires [[2d6]] rounds to Repair. One-shot devices are wasted with no effect, and cause Fatigue if they were rubbed on, injected, inhaled, or swallowed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[3,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hO6JLRczLZ6aD9s9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Minor:</strong> The item fails to work until a Repair roll is made as an action. One-use items have no effect and are consumed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[5,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"_id":"XaPuEvIzGq6PHnbH"}
{"name":"Telegraph Results","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.deadlands-rules.Tables-Deadlands.CfNHayELal2dLUif"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"Whenever your posse sends or receives a telegraph and you want to mess with them, roll a d20 on the table below and see what happens.","results":[{"_id":"dtuhELBXevinckiS","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The message goes through fine.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":9,"range":[1,9],"drawn":false},{"_id":"FKLWefbc9hxOKVCy","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The receiving telegraph station receives no incoming messages for the next 1d4 hours. Unless they're expecting a message or are a larger station, they likely have no clue they've \"gone deaf.\"","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[10,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"SQYScuJTwGp5AOpe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The gremlins respond with a random telegraph from another station elsewhere along the line. A desperate posse might telegraph for the authorities and receive a message that, \"AUNT MINNIE ARRIVES BY STAGE ON TUESDAY.\"","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BK3RGoc8mPHPqmEs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Gremlins rearrange the words of the telegram to cause as much trouble and mischief as possible.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BxM0b3eMxIcrx8Vf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The gremlins change the message so that it's insulting and rude, but echo the right confirmation from the receiver.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LxQpXYFRdaHDkkFe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The message goes to the wrong station. They might ask for the location of a contact in Dodge but get a reply back from Lost Angels. If the message isn't specific, the operator won't know it went to the wrong city.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"nRdyCLiA8oo30K8D","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The gremlins pretend to be a deranged operator at the other end. They reply to the message with crude taunts and cryptic responses. Feel free to do just about anything you want to vex the heroes as much as possible. Think like a lowdown, mischievous gremlin, Marshal!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"_id":"jLjIjqFvboF2QLK8"}
